Allow NIL for the optional WORLD argument of webkit-web-view-evaluate-javascript.

The function body already does `(if world ...)` to dispatch between the
"in-world" and the default code paths.  However the (declaim (ftype ...))
declaration above types WORLD as `string`, which makes SBCL signal

  Warning: Error on GTK thread:
    The value NIL is not of type STRING when binding CL-WEBKIT2::WORLD

at runtime under strict type-checking when Nyxt (or any caller) invokes
this function without a world.  Relaxing the type to `(or null string)`
matches the function's actual contract.

--- a/webkit2/webkit2.web-view.lisp
+++ b/webkit2/webkit2.web-view.lisp
@@ -276,7 +276,7 @@

 (declaim (ftype (function (webkit-web-view string &optional
                                            (or null (function (t t)))
-                                           (or null (function (condition))) string))
+                                           (or null (function (condition))) (or null string)))
                 webkit-web-view-evaluate-javascript))
 (defun webkit-web-view-evaluate-javascript (web-view javascript
                                             &optional call-back error-call-back world)
